---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import { SITE_TITLE, SITE_DESCRIPTION } from '../consts';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <BaseHead title={SITE_TITLE} description={SITE_DESCRIPTION} />
  </head>
  <body>
    <Header />
    <main class="prose mx-auto px-4 py-8">
      <h1>👋 Hey, I’m Ryan Laird</h1>
      <p>
        Welcome to <strong>rjmlaird.dev</strong> — my digital workspace for building, testing, and documenting tools that bridge <strong>space, sustainability</strong>, and <strong>software development</strong>.
      </p>
      <p>
        This site is where I experiment with integrations, automation workflows, and technical approaches that support sustainable growth in the space sector. It’s a reflection of my work in building smarter, leaner, and more ethical digital systems.
      </p>

      <h2>🛠️ What You’ll Find Here</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Project insights:</strong> technical breakdowns of dev tools and SaaS automations</li>
        <li><strong>Custom workflows:</strong> syncing systems like HubSpot, Notion, Stripe, and beyond</li>
        <li><strong>Space-sector dev:</strong> tools designed for transparency, tracking, and scalability</li>
        <li><strong>Markdown-powered blog:</strong> thoughts on digital sustainability and developer ops</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>📚 Recent Work</h2>
      <p>
        You can browse live projects and dev logs under <a href="/projects">Projects</a>, or read in-depth posts in the <a href="/blog">Blog</a>. These include everything from SDG tracking dashboards to GitHub-integrated tooling for content pipelines.
      </p>

      <h2>📬 Get in Touch</h2>
      <p>
        I’m always interested in collaborations or conversations around <strong>tech for good</strong>, <strong>space systems</strong>, and the future of sustainable development tooling. Reach out at <a href="mailto:hello@rjmlaird.dev">hello@rjmlaird.dev</a> or connect via <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/rjmlaird/">LinkedIn</a>.
      </p>

    </main>
    <Footer />
  </body>
</html>